place_description: Upscale grocery store chain with an old-world vibe offers local produce, prepared eats, wine & more.

reviews_data.review_text: Your store had the best and freshest big blueberry pie anywhere. What happened I can not find it in any Fresh Markets since last year.

I have been an original fresh market fan until your advertising buy 7 items, 8th free anything. That was a lie and misleading . Now you are advertising the same deal except 10 items, 11th free. The customer does not get to choose. The computer does. The add is a lie and very misleading. I bought everything there except cleaning and everyday paper products. Ray Barry would be disappointed in new ownership. Respectfully, rebecca walsh

Great informative Staff  willing to assist you with
Finding what you need .
Wonderful grocery store

This morning, at 10 AM, I went to buy the side of prime ribeye you advertised with a specially discounted price. I was told that the store did not have prime cut, only premium choice.

Corporate does it again.
What's in your walk-in?
A little pricey but the organic snacks here are AMAZING

Yesterday I shopped at Strawberry Hill location after seeing 20% off produce day. I shop here regularly and spent $200+yesterday as I do regularly here. I am so disappointed in the produce.  Clearly they were moving older produce out. I bought a large pkg of strawberries and had to throw 1/2 out with rotted undersides. Same with expensive blueberries.  Avacado was brown runny mush this morning. Orange sections were soft and not firm as usual. The veggies all seem to be fine. I love the store and will continue to shop there as I have never had this kind of experience before. But avoid discounts on Produce on Thursdays.
They have a little big meal that is to die for . I iterally for the best combinations for a low budget. I got crab cakes ,kerigold butter ,,salad, a box of pasta ,and garlic knots for $20
Nice visit. Employees were helpful
Love this store
One of your workers was stealing food and had a horrible attitude his name was Delano Deshawn heath and I heard he tried to sleep with one of his coworkers and lied on them when he got rejected
Brandon has helped my family twice during busy times - an absolute treasure of a human. Grateful for the wonderful team here!

We picked up a Thanksgiving meal. The staff was friendly. Virtually no wait time. Reviewed our order with us, which came in a reusable shopping box/bag.  Ate a few hours later. The food exceeded our expectations.

My phone number never works for loyalty program, they don't give out cards, and there is no internet/cell service in the store so you can't even look up your loyalty number. Also no split discounts for buying less than the number of items on the sale , e.g. yogurt 10/$10 should be dollar each but if you only get 5, you are paying 7.50.  Staff seemed well aware of the issues, but no solution offered.

I was helped by Iris today at the register. She didn't greet me, and when she rang up my bottle of wine, said in a borderline aggressive tone, "I'm going to need to see some ID." Her tone caught me off guard because I'm 27, but I may look younger to some for whatever reason. I felt that I was treated with less respect, and that she might've thought I was trying to trick her. Incredibly, the man behind me forgot his ID, and she still rang him up. I did not feel welcome during my visit.

Also, it seems the plant section has been forgotten. Many beautiful plants were yellow or dying which is a shame because it's a good selection.
The most professional people i have ever met! The first is definitely fresh. This is my new grocery store! Everyone was so friendly and helpful
Quality foods and no long lines at lunchtime.
Fresh and quality products

Fresh Market truly exemplifies exceptional service. From the moment I stepped through their doors, I was greeted with warm smiles and helpful staff members. The employees went above and beyond to assist me in finding the products I needed and provided valuable recommendations. Their knowledge about the different products was impressive, and they were always willing to answer my questions. The checkout process was seamless, with efficient and friendly cashiers. Fresh Market's commitment to providing a positive shopping experience is evident in every interaction. I highly recommend Fresh Market for their outstanding customer service and dedication to customer satisfaction.
Great quality food and beautiful interior.  Service from cashiers is good as well.
Health food , but some stuff are over priced
Lovely store, amazing produce options, fun candy and flowers.
I love their meat the only problem is that they are expensive
Quality products and good service but pricey.
It's a great store. It can be pricey but, if you like good food it's worth it
They have things that are hard to find elsewhere. They are never cheap, but their sales and BOGO free offers make those prices reasonable. Staff is very helpful. Quality is high.

I would like to take time to a recognize Brandon who went above and beyond during my many visits at Fresh Market on Providence Rd. Brandon always greets me with a welcoming smile every time. He takes pride in his job, and handles each of his customers with great care! Brandon has such a positive attitude, and I'm blown away at how awesome his customer service is, that I had to make sure to write a review about him! Brandon informed of the Fresh Market Ultimate Loyalty Experience, and I had to sign up right on the spot, to make sure I am not missing out on any savings Fresh Market has to offer. I am very grateful for Brandon and his awesomeness! From your loyal Fresh Market customer
-Jan.

I needed lamb and failed after going to 3 other groceries stores (we'll call them Amazon foods, TajMahTeeter, and  flublix). The one guy was incredibly helpful and immediately figured out a solution for my dinner party. Super friendly, helpful and fast!
Thanks guys!
Good foods.  Lots of great choices.  Love the deli and bakery!
Great place to shop. Friendly employees Great produce, meat department in groceries

Decent selection of groceries. For being "high-end" and "fresh" they could have a better sushi selection. Not everyone likes avocado, or spicy rolls. Have someone there that rolls them for on the spot orders. Make a normal roll with no avocado and not spicy. They would make more money. Invest in your customers wants and needs and in turn they spend more money. Simple. Take notes from northern Wegmans Markets, fresh on the spot semi custom orders. Can at least ask for no avocado and they make it. Buy three rolls everytime I'm in there.
One of my favorite spots in the city for over 20 years.
Love the bakery and deli. They make the best roasted chicken salad around. Just ate a Yule log that was worth going off my diet
Quick place.

I absolutely love this store! It smells amazing from the moment you enter and everything is so visually appealing.
Some of my favorite things to buy here....Kona blend coffee, rotisserie chicken salad from the deli, baked goods are all delicious! I also love the Root brand candles and the plants and fresh flowers!
Friendly people who work there are always willing to help you!

Bad on so many levels. Went to get a few quick things one evening. Had my young son in tow. We had 3 things and went to the checkout line. The lines were long and slow. So we waited. Finally our turn came and I entered my phone number for the Loyalty rewards. It did not work. I tried a few other numbers, none seemed to work. Now the line is really long behind me and my items would have qualified for the discount. So I asked the cashier to enter a number so I do not hold up the line any further. She told me to fill out a new form. I told her that there is a long line and I don't want to hold up everybody for something so simple. She said not to worry. But worry I did. I just paid full price for everything so I did not hold up other patrons who were waiting patiently. JUST AWFUL CUSTOMER SERVICE. In any other store, the employees would be ok doing this, but not here. They just need better training, better management, and better understanding of the issues. Fortunately, Harris Teeter and Publix both are very close and I promise you neither of those stores would have done that.

And before posting this, I went on their website to rely this episode to see if they would respond. CRICKETS! Just goes to show how much they value their customers. You lost a customer for good.
Always have a nice experience!  Everyone is friendly and helpful

Told the cashier to discount the oj because sell by date was 5/13/22 and she told me i cant sell it and now it goes to waste. Shame on you fresh market for not doing markdowns and just throwing everything away. Their bake chicken is overprice and has wine...come on not everyone can consume wine! Everything is overpriced

I've only shopped here once. Highest prices in the area and thee people who work there were kind of weird.

If you ask for the sushi man to make some for you, forget, they will not look in your face.

A wonderful place to shop for, produce, meats, and bakery items. A very large selection of prepared foods to choose from. Enjoyed shopping there.

Today me and my family came in to shop on a regular day. We got our groceries per usual and headed over to the checkout line. We were there met with a man named Raymond, and all seemed normal until he said, "let's see how fast I can do this". We laughed. But soon would that laugher turn into awe. Raymond began his scanning, but in the blink of an eye he was already finished. He was moving so fast that everything was a blur, and once he had started he was already done, ready for us to pay. We sat there, with jaws gaping open in complete shock. Laws of physics were broken. Light speed had been reached. I now know that something CAN be in two places at once thanks to Raymond. The next time you visit the Providence Road Fresh Market please ask for Raymond, so you too can have the life-changing experience that we just did. I truly believe that my third eye has been opened. Nirvana has been achieved.
Freshest produce around.
The market was fresh...who knew?

Another disappointing visit to this grocery store. After waiting for a while at the counter to be helped, I finally gave up and decided to just grab a "fresh" salad (cause I had to get back to work). Opened up the salad and shook the dressing in with the salad and started munching. Was immediately weirded out by an odd texture and taste. The flat cheese was super old and shake. Gross. Wasted time, money, and now I don't have dinner. This place needs to get their stuff together.

This was my preferred local grocery store about a year ago, thanks in part to friendly people and consistent availability of produce, including meats.  Things have changed since new management came in and construction of the new Fresh Market was announced.  The employees remained and are still the best part of the grocery store but the quality of produce has fallen and availability of it is inconsistent, including the meat department.  I believe the trucks deliver over the weekend so my general experience of availability degrades throughout the work week.  I've lost count how many times I've come to this store and something as simple as lettuce, tomatillos, or even chicken is not available.  Complaints generally solicit an apology at best, or a finger pointed towards management at worst.  The possibility of change feels rather futile until the new store opens.

I still walk here regularly to get some things but if you need something in a pinch, you're rolling the dice on disappointment.  There are two nearby Harris Teeters in the meantime, with a Publix on the way.
